ANUJA is a joyous story
about hope, resilience, the powerful bonds of sisterhood, and the profound =
impact of lifting up those who may not have a voice or opportunity. The sho=
rt follows a gifted nine-year-old girl, alongside her sister Palak, as they=
 work in a back-alley garment factory. When a teacher offers Anuja a chance=
 to attend an elite boarding school, the sisters must navigate challenges t=
hat test their resilience and bond, culminating in a decision faced by coun=
tless young girls worldwide.

=C2=A0

Produced in partnership with the Salaam Baalak Trust, a non-profit organiza=
tion who provides food, shelter, and education to thousands of street and w=
orking children in New Delhi. Lead actress Sajda Pathan, who plays the role=
 of Anuja, is one of these children.

=C2=A0

